{"in": {"title": "Sometimes A Leaf", "subtitle": "<span id=\"tr_lore_id\">katya</span>", "lines": ["SCENE: https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/melancholic-poe.mp3 (no wait)", "KATYA: Sometimes a leaf will fall&nbsp;", "KATYA: ever so silently and softly that", "KATYA: a caterpillar curled up on it won't even know", "KATYA: it's time to crawl away and find a new home.&nbsp;", "KATYA: Sometimes a leaf will fall", "KATYA: when it's still green and fleshy,", "KATYA: with a thud, still plump with juice", "KATYA: thinking everyone's thinking", "KATYA: \"How ungraceful, that leaf!\"&nbsp;", "KATYA: Sometimes a leaf will fall", "KATYA: when it's spent and dry", "KATYA: and the slightest whiff of an autumn breeze", "KATYA: could pluck it from", "KATYA: its home, the only place it's ever known.&nbsp;", "KATYA: Sometimes a leaf is blown about", "KATYA: here and there, up and down,", "KATYA: before reaching land,", "KATYA: like a sailor on a skiff in a storm.", "KATYA: Sometimes a leaf will fall", "KATYA: after it's had a chance to wave", "KATYA: in the wind and touch its neighbors one last time.", "KATYA: It's late October and the leaves are turning.", "KATYA: But I haven't turned a single one. I sit", "KATYA: in the gentle shade of the maidenhair", "KATYA: Ginkgo being amazed at all these", "KATYA: leaves instead of reading this fat book", "KATYA: with a thousand iron pages. I promised", "KATYA: myself I would finish it today.", "KATYA: But this yellow leaf,", "KATYA: the exact color of churned butter my", "KATYA: (slow) sister, before her fall,", "KATYA: (slow) used to make on lazy Sunday mornings,", "KATYA: (slow) quietly feather-waltzes on to the page I should", "KATYA: (slow) have turned an hour ago. It's strange", "KATYA: (slow) how one leaf reminds you of another.", "KATYA: (slow) Sometimes a leaf", "KATYA: (x-slow) makes the best bookmark."], "speaker_map": {"NARRATOR": "Joanna", "SCENE": "Joanna", "KATYA": "Ivy"}}, "out": {"cache_id": "575c3b4cc62ed0976a574c